text:
When my brothers had passed all of their exams and were able to  á
graduate from their courses.
When I was caught in an elevator and it got stuck between floors.
When I was put into a tennis team below my standard.
When my father died.

When I have seen people very drunk and making fools of á
themselves.

When my present boyfriend asked me initially to go out with him I á
had waited a long time for this to occur.

When somebody broke into our home one night when my mother was á
out, and my sister and I had just gone to bed.

When my sister lost my favourite jumper at a party and failed to á
tell me for several days after it happened.

When my father passed away of cancer, I was extremely saddened. á
He was not very old, which made matters worse. The actual death á
was horrendous, but the moving funeral saddened me more so.

When walking along the beach with my boyfriend, we saw 2 people á
having sex on the sand dunes in full view of everyone. It was the á
fact that they chose that area in which to have sex, that á
disgusted me.

I stayed at the Coast for a weekend with friends. My brother came á
to drive me home, but was rude, and in a hurry to rejoin his á
friends. I was embarrassed because the family involved was á
extremely nice, and hospitable to him.

When I saw my brother in Church, and publically accept Jesus á
Christ as his saviour and Lord.

I was seven years old and swimming outside the flags at the Gold á
Coast. I was caught in a rip and taken out about 100 m. I á
couldn't swim too well, but an older friend (17) swam out and á
saved me.

While at school I had to write an essay for doing something wrong á
that I didn't do. I wrote the essay about how I was mistreated and á
got Saturday morning detention along with a few other kids, but á
they didn't show up.
When one of my closest friends died unexpectantly.

When I saw a male engineer one year and came back to find he was á
now a female (I don't know it/them personally).

On holidays - just driving along a road beautiful scenery. Just á
with my boyfriend - not really talking but just feeling á
overwhelmed.
Good news about a sick relative.
Walking in the dark by myself.
Getting terrible meals, but paying heaps for them.
When felt lonely about writing my family.
Person talking about a situation while eating.

When I received my TE Score and my acceptance from University - á
it had been a goal since I left the bank a year earlier.
Every time I see a spider or a snake.

My younger brother and I had been fighting over the TV/Video. He á
kept on turning it on and off every 2 seconds and was not á
listening to my authority and was being cheeky. We fought and I á
ended up in tears - he'd won.
The first time I left home.

On a camp - boys and girls in one cabin. One guy forced himself á
upon another girl and was having intercourse, while the girl in á
the bunk beneath was pretending to be asleep and not be ill.

Can't remember specific event - besides just being moderately á
happy until a year or so ago.
Left alone in dark when young.
Can't remember exact example.
Close relative is dying of cancer - found out last week.

Doctors ignored relative who complained about pain, and is now á
dying of cancer.
After the fact that made me ashamed I felt sadness.

A person that eat half of a cockroach in a cake without knowing á
it.

When finally I found a place to live, I felt relieved, predicting á
changes in my life, and I became happy.
When I dreamed that I was being attacked by a friend.
When I was left by the person I loved without any reason.
To fight with a sister and to know that she doesn't care.
To be kissed by soembody I didn't expect to.

I felt it when I received a letter telling that I had been á
classified in a national concourse of p... I felt happy and á
vanity about it.

I felt fear when once I was asleep and dreamed that I was dying á
asfixiated by a cardiac attack, I was afraid and woke up á
desperate. Altough I wasn't afraid of death I was afraid.

I feel it when I see that somebody is traying to made a stupid of á
me.

I felt it when I was at home and saw a discussion without sense á
between my parents.

When I see all the putridness of people. The fact is the catarrh á
and spits that whash the streets of S.Paulo.
When I asked my girlfriend to marry me.

When I almost drowned myself in the municipal swimming pool that á
I use to go almost not excaping.

I was with my girlfriend when some guys that I don't like made á
fuss at my girl.
The death of my grandfather.

To go through the underground way at suburb station of LAPA. Poor á
people and the ambulants badly dressed up in a passage badly á
kept.
When I met a friend that I hadn't seen for some time.
When I got in jungle where there was a great number of snakes.
When an unknown person provoked me verbaly and physically.
When my team lost a championship.
A dirty person, smelling bad and unknown laying on me.

When I began to date a boy with whom I am till now. This was 16 á
months ago.
I learned that my girlfriend had been unjustly missed from work.
I got separated from the man I loved.

An acquaintance of mine revealed himself in a light unexpected to á
me.

When I took my entrance exams successfully and also when I got my á
school leaving certificate because the delivering ceremony was á
extremely official.

When I was to sit for my first entrance exam. I had fear of a á
possible failure.

I was indignant at the unimpartiality shown by the referees at á
the football match between Bulgaria and France.
When I got separated from the man I loved so much.

When I was watching some scenes from the Bertoluchi's film á
"Twentieth Century".
When I was admitted to the Sofia University.
When I come home late at night.
When I talk to silly, petty-minded and unmanageable people.
When my friend (girl) went abroad for two years.
When I happen to witness some sadistic acts.
I was admitted to the University and a niece was born to me.
I was bitten by a dog.
My grandfather's funeral.
I was alone at home on New Year's Eve.
I was on a walk with my child when I met a drunk woman.
My admittance to the University.
A grenade blew out next to me.
An unjust calumny concerning me.
Unrealisation of the desired profession (aviator).
Disgust with a subordinate.
Winning Queensland Chess Championship.

When in a car accident where car was total wipe off (wipe out, or á
write off).
With self at losing an important game that I should have won.
Death of grandfather (unexpected).

Someone smoking on Electric train (Electric trains are á
non-smoking) with alcohol smell coming from person.

Receiving a very personal letter from a lady that I like, which á
revealed that she was more enthusiastic about me than I had á
thought possible.
Introducing myself at a first tutorial this year at University.

I was angry at a University tutorial when an ignorant loudmouth á
persisted in trying to dominate the conversation.

I left my home in Melbourne to come to Q'land to study and before á
I hopped in the car I hugged my mother and shook hands with my á
father. Sensing immediately my father's sadness, I also had a á
flood of the same emotion.
When one of my parents verbally, personally abused the other.
Being in love for the first time.

As a child - stepping on a rusty nail - being told that I might á
get tetanus.

As a child - about 8 years old - walking across a paddock - being á
set upon by another boy who claimed it was "his land" - being á
intimidated by the boy - crying, being punched, etc.
As a child - having a dog - it getting a disease and dying.

Being in a Malaysian city with my girlfriend coming out of a á
picture theatre - seeing her rush up to a taxi that a very old á
sick man was trying to get to. Seeing her take over the taxi.

When I achieved my first 6 at University after a long string of á
3's, 4's and 5's (7 is the highest mark awarded, 3 is a conceded á
pass).

One night going downstairs, and hearing a strong stirring of á
brances, which was not the wind.

I was informed by my flatmate that, when we'd moved into our á
flat, she'd expected us to buy our food separetely - this event á
actually happened some 5 months after our sharing began. Prior to á
this, she had said nothing.

Having to decide on a termination of a pregnancy, after á
discussing it with friends, family and the man involved.

When a friend didn't invite her own parents to her Graduation á
ceremony.

When I was a child, my beloved cat gave birth to four beautiful á
little kittens. Before she had them, she came up to me and I á
followed her out, then witnessed them being born.

On embarking on University life. I came from a different city and á
did not know anybody at the Uni. I was frightened because my well á
known and loved friends, also all my security had been taken á
away.

When my brothers were being cruel to my boyfriend, because his á
flat-mate bent back one of my brother's fingers. It wasn't his á
fault.

Upon moving away from home for the first time to a different á
city, I felt no longer "under the wing" of my parents even though á
they would always be there to help me. I felt a sense of loss, I á
was now all alone in the world, responsible for my own actions.

I was sitting at a rock concert, listening to an extremely loud á
band. A tiny baby in a crawler had been left by his young mother, á
right out in the sun next to a speaker, and was screaming - á
probably in pain.

The weekend after I argued with my parents I went home again and á
they couldn't have been nicer. As soon as I walked in, Mum kissed á
me, then Dad, and thanked me for the birthday presents I'd left á
for him, including a very sentimental birthday card.

Before Uni started, I had to leave home and take up residence in á
Brisbane (the "big smoke") leaving home, my family, and moving to á
such a big place was quite intimidating at first, and I was á
anxious about it.

My flatmate was asking questions about my relationship with my á
boyfriend, whether I wasn't treating him as unfairly as I claimed á
he'd been treating me. As a result, I was angered, and became á
defensive.

A very close friend from Victoria visited me over the holidays. á
Having enjoyed his company immensely over 10 short days, I was á
overwhelmed by sadness when he left to return to Victoria.á

One of my flatmates and I came back to the flat Monday morning, á
to find a real Mess, left by the guy we share with.

Joy of giving birth, and of sharing that joy with my husband. á
Moments of complete happiness and feelings of so much love.

Attempted rape by 5 guys - held my arms behind my back and á
molested me, constantly threatening to beat me. Penetration did á
not occur as the driver of the car stopped that.

Anger at doctors for their treatment of me after giving birth. á
They left part of placenta behind and I bled heavily for twelve á
weeks - due to this, I felt weak and emotional, and they said I á
needed psychiatric treatment and give me no support.

When my son was diagnosed as having CEREBRAL PALSY, at age 5. He á
would have to endure so much labelling, stigma and discrimination, á
even though his case was relatively mild.

I have an adopted Aboriginal sister I felt disgust due to the á
racism she has been subjected to.

Receiving notification that I had made a successful application á
to the Speech Therapy course at Uni, gave me a very good feelig á
of achievment and joy.
Not included on questionnaire.

My ex-boyfriend began to date my best friend. After they had been á
seeing each other, I found out that he had been sleeping with á
another girl, without my friend knowing, I told my friend what he á
had been doing behind her back.

My mother left my father for his best friend, and he moved to á
Papua New Guinea. Despite the fact that I am closer to my father á
than to anyone else in my family, I had to move in with my á
mother, and say good-bye to my father, not knowing when I would á
see him again.

When I discovered my mother had been having an affair with my á
father's best friend, and then ran away with him without even á
speaking to me about what she was doing letting me come home from á
school simply to find her gone. I was filled with disgust and á
contempt.

Seeing a close friend who had just returned from twelve months á
overseas.

Finding myself alone in a public toilet block with a man known to á
have had great psychological disturbances.

After seeing an "uncertain" child work on a model for several á
hours, I watched a "bully" of the same age destroy it, telling á
the child that it was worthless.

Leaving home to move closer to University. As an oldest child, á
this experience was traumatic for both my parents and myself.

Viewing the results of senseless vandalism to a local primary á
school.

When I finished my exams after 12th Grade, I was worried about á
getting a T.E. Score high enough for Physiotherapy. When I found á
that I had been accepted I was ecstatic, or more appropriately, á
could jump for joy.

When going for my driver's licence for the third time, because á
everything, it seemed, hinged on getting it. I was really nervous, á
and the testing Officer made me a little afraid as well. There á
were lots of things to worry about. I passed however.

When a so-called friend let me down, when she promised to tell me á
when a certain concert was occurring, and that she'd get me á
tickets. I was really looking forward to it. She did nothing, á
just told me out of the blue one day what a fantastic concert it á
was going to be.

When my family heard that my Mother's cousin who lives in á
England wrote us to tell that he had cancer of the lymph glands.

When I found out how the people of Ethiopia were starving and á
their government was spending millions on celebrating being in á
power so many years. Then I saw all these people on TV needing á
food, etc.

Two years ago, somebody I like very much wanted to give up his á
studies. I tried to make him understand the importance of what he á
was going to do, not only of the difficulty to find a job but also á
because he will decrease his culture etc. This person made the á
test to the college entrance examination and to our great joy we á
found out that he succeded in entering at the University.

One night, when I got out from the University I saw two strange á
people near my car. When I got near, they moved away, and then á
came close again. I had a feeling that they were assaulters. á
After I left I discovered that the windshield was broken.

One day in a crossroad somebody crashed my car. I got out and á
this person laughed at me. I felt such a great anger that I got á
in my car and went away.

I don't know why suddenly I thought that what I was feeling for á
my boyfriend was not really love. After almost three years being á
together, this matter of fact shaked me and I felt a great sorrow á
that I can call sadness.

Returning home in the late afternoon I saw an indecent act made á
by a man with the purpose that I saw it.
When I entered at the University.

One night I and my friends went to the cemetery. We stopped the á
car in front of the wall and suddenly the grave digger appeared á
over the wall looking like a ghost. I was already afraid and á
almost died.

When one teacher unjustly gave me zero in a test saying that I á
was cribbing.
When my grandmother died.

I went to a restaurant with my boyfriend for dinner. There we saw á
a couple. the man of the couple was a negro and he hadn't manners á
for eat.

When in the end of a semester I got the approval in a matter that á
I judged very difficult.

Crossing a street of several ways the cars began to move and I á
thought that I was going to be trampled.

I went to the school library and asked for a book, but the á
librarian told me that there wasn't such. However when an other á
colleague asked for it she gave it to him.

Some colleagues decided to go out on a Saturday not inviting me á
to decide either the place nor the time.

A teacher giving a test was called by a student by his first á
name. He (the teacher) said that he didn't give him this liberty.

The situation in which I felt happiest in my life was when á
I was with the person I love for the first time.
Fear of thief.
I feel anger when somebody forbids me to do something.
I felt sad when I was despised by another person.
I felt disgust of dirty.

When I got through the examination for my driver licence, and á
when I finished I knew I had passed it.

I was inside the car with my husband and we were assaulted with a á
gun at 10 o'clock in the evening.
When they changed my office to another room without my agreement.

I couldn't sleep, and began to remind of my childhood. We are many á
sisters and at that time we were spanked a lot and I don't know á
why I started to remind of the spanks they and I had had, their á
shouts when this happened.

When I red a report in the magazine VESA about an Iranian telling á
what she had lived in the prisons in Iran. I felt disgust about á
that people.

I was in ILHA GRANDE with a wonderful sun, with wonderful people, á
with a wonderful sea, with a wonderful boy.

When I was looking for a job I felt a lot of fear but the fear á
was greater when I found it.

This feeling occurred to me when my colleague entered in G.V. á
(University) and I didn't.

When I applied for the college entrance examination to FUVEST, á
and I wasn't approved in the second fase.

I had this feeling when I met a girl, not that she was dirty but á
she was to "fresh", dump and childish.

I felt happy when my mother borrowed me the car in order to let á
me go out alone for the first time.

I felt afraid when I smoked maryhuana for the first time in my á
life with a lot of friends in the middle of the street at day á
brake.

I felt anger when I had a fight with my father, and he beated me. á
My mother came to help me (because I was beeing beated) and he á
also beated my mother.

It happened when I lost two very intimate friends in a car á
accident.
I felt disgust of my father when I knew he had a lover.
Always when I am well succeded.
When there is danger nearby.
I feel anger when things don't come out as I wish.
When I couldn't go for a trip with my friends in a holiday.
Disgust of drunkers and of blood.

When there was a possibility of getting on better in professional á
life. I valorized very much this aspect. People showed me this á
possibility, not the real fact (even because until now ...)

When I was curious about it and went to a spiritism session with a á
friend. I had already been there other times (many times when I á
was younger) but that day, even if I don't believe in á
spiritism I was terribly afraid that something would happen to me á
(sort of incorporation !).

When they denied a job to a person that I propsed giving political á
reasons that has nothing to do directly with the professional á
level.

During an informal talk with a friend when we talk about the life á
of another person, a common friend, that is in a situation of not á
being able to assume certain problems that he decided to solve, á
that is, she herself suggested the problems and decided to solve á
them but didn't get it until the moment.

When my friends and I were camping in a weekend, and with little á
food, we met a middle age couple from a small town that invited á
us to eat in their house. Their house was small, badly built with á
old and dirty forniture and utensils. The problem was with pans, á
and dishes, and even the food.
When I got a wedding ring of diamond from the boy I loved.
Afraid of getting alone without friends, without anybody.
When they stole my dark blue tennis.

When I became conscious that men don't wnat anything they don't á
have a goal. They have: sex, but this isn't important.

When I went in a clinical hospital and saw in what conditions á
people are attended there.

When I met again a great friend and talked a little while with á
him. When I see again another I miss.

I feel afraid of the way a great friend looks at me, and also a á
little afraid of the directions that it's going.

I felt anger of a friend when she met "a date" and become nervous á
and pest as she always gets when she meets him.

When I knew almost the same day about two great friends of mine á
that had serious existential crisis, and mainly when I notice á
that I'm in the same situation that they are, but I didn't á
realize it.

When some friends and I get acquainted a guy during vacations I á
thought he was disgusted and "a friend" of mine for whom I feel a á
little disgust wanted to stay with him.
When I entered University.

I have been afraid several times. What marked me was that I á
almost didn't enter University.

I'm crazy about football. When my team lost a goal in the Paulist á
championship, and so it lost the classifications.
When my grandmother, my second mother died.
When a girl that I liked didn't accept my curting.

When I met a girl and asked her for a date and she agreed, (I á
thought this girl would never like me), this was an emotion of á
joy.

The same fact about the girl (22 years, married - guilt - á
disgust), the fear was the main factor in our relationship.

About the car (sadness) I felt anger the way I acted after á
negotiating it.
To buy a car and didn't like the business and the car.

I met a girl (22 years old), married. I liked her. I asked her á
for a date and I kissed her. I discovered that she lived nearby á
where I passed every day. I got amused thinking that her husband á
would be ... or me . I didn't talked to her anymore.

I felt joy when I red my name in the list of the approved in the á
entrance college examination.

I was visiting my parents in law when the house was invaded by á
three strange men, and they committed an armed assault.

Nearby the end of the year my wife and I were having a car ride, á
when it appears another vehicle, driven by a drunk driver and á
provokes an accident.

To have a friend who I didn't see for months, and under the á
circumstances that I met him made me feel happy, and perhaps á
because it has been one of the good things that I learned with á
this friend.

When I left a carnaval ball at 4 o'clock a.m. I was alone in a á
foreign city and I had to go back home, when a guy appeared and á
tried to "catch me".

The fact that I hadn't been informed about something and I had the á
greatest trust in this person.

A friend of mine lent me his apartment for holidays and besides á
this he was a fine person. Months later I knew that he died á
tragically in a moto accident. He was very young, and I felt sad á
and couldn't believe it (until today).

In contact with a poor family of northeast it was offered to me a á
crab to eat at my request. But the fact that this crab was á
prepared antihygienically and his appearence was also á
antihygienically it caused me disgust but I ate it anyway.
When, after a long time of searching I got my first job.

After some time of work I was transferred to another place and in á
an other quite harder job.

When I used to go to my chief asking about any doubt about the job á
and he didn't care, didn't answer me, leaving me speaking alone.

When I knew that a person that I liked very much didn't react the á
way I would like to, even that I knew about his feelings for me.

When I knew that a person who I didn't like, had about me other á
feelings.
When a person that I like very much got near to me.

I was at home alone, and heard noises on the roof, and doorknobs, á
and drawers.

When a person is privileged in account of situations that are á
unjust, and disloyal to colleagues and friends.

When I was betrayed by a friend, and decided to stay apart form á
her.

After a serie of facts that occurred between a colleague and me I á
started to feel a certain necessity to get apart and I didn't want á
to see her anymore.

I made the college entrance examinations for P.U.C. It was what I á
wanted more. When the first list came out I got frustrated. I á
wasn't in. When the second list came out without hopes I started á
to read the newspaper and my name was thre. I was in the bus and á
felt like crying so that everybody could hear me. The cry was hold, á
and 1982 became forever a mask in my life.

I remember when I was a child of a storm that made me terribly á
afraid. I thought that the house was coming down and that in the á
next day I would be dead. Everybody was awake and I stayed all á
night in bed without falling asleep.

Once in my work it happened a fight between the person in charge and me. I á
got so angry and spoke out everything I felt at the moment.

I remember the day my father died. I was 11 years old and my á
sadness was so great that until today I remember everything á
about that day, from the clothes I was wearing to the reactions of people, á
the despair of my mother and brother. It marked me a lot and was á
the greatest sadness I felt.

I was sitting in school, waiting for my sister to go home. Suddenly a á
boy put fire in a paper and threw it were I was sitting. The á
paper didn't get me, but I felt terribly disgusted at this á
cowardliness and irresponsibility that caused a great á
discussion. We went to the director and he, drunk as always, said á
that I was ... attention in school. I felt disgust of this á
situation, and of the persons implicated in it.

The day I received the key of my apartment and we could enter in á
it, for my fiancT and I had bought it yet in plans, and it seemed á
to us that this was almost impossible to happen.

I had a driver licence but I didn't drive for a long time, than I á
started to drive again, and had to get into hard transit and á
highways.

When my boss cut off my vacations saying that in that month it á
wouldn't be possible, and after some time he let another girl á
take vacations that month. The anger was because of the á
resentment. Resulting from our bad relationship.

My fiancT's family was adopting a 5 years old boy. I felt á
myself close to him as I never felt before. After some time his á
mother demanded the care of the kid and we were obliged to send á
him back.

There is a girl at my work that doesn't take care much of her á
hygiene she comes always with her hair oiled, a not very agreable á
smell, and a bad appearance. Beside this she tries to be nice.

It was when a friend took me to a place and gave me as a gift my á
astrologycal map with the explanations of a psychologist.

When I was dreaming that I was being chased, in the upmost of á
horror the door of the closed felt down synchronicaly with the á
dream scare.

When my mother slapped me in the face, I felt anger at that á
moment.

When I deeply felt that I could lose the person I love best á
because of my foolishness.

I felt disgust toward meat when I felt sick with the steak after á
a week only on meat.

In a day when at work, in school, and relationships came out as I á
wanted, and I was recognized in my work.

When I woke up in the middle of the night because of a dream, it á
wasn't a nightmare, it was an uninteligible dream in wich I woke á
because of a certain end.
When I was robbed in a bus.
When I try to get closer at a person and she misinterpreted me.
When I felt the smell of industries that pollute.

I was travelling in the South of Brasil, near the end of the á
year. I was well settled with 3 friends. At the evening of 31 M., á
somebody, also with us, took from his purse pints of all colours, á
and the 4 of us, and other friends, that were at the same beach, á
painted each other and we went to the beach with champagne.

I was walking from my friend's house, a few blocks from my house, when a á
car began to follow me. He waited I passed by it rotateed a little and á
stopped on my way. I changed completely my way and the car went á
on following me until I turned at a corner and running I hid in a á
garden of a house, waiting for the car to pass by. I went back home á
terribly afraid.

One day I lent my tennis I just had washed to my sister because á
she asked it. I asked her not to soil it as I had just washed it. á
Next day I looked at the tennis, and it was dirty with wax. She á
could not have soiled it. It was lack of consideration. I felt á
very angry.

The second time I went to the entrance exam to V.S.P. and á
didn't get approved.

I was travelling, we were 15 person, one of them I met at the á
travel and didn't like her. One night I was asleep while she and á
her friends were talking too loud in the kitchen. I got up to ask for á
silence and since that day I felt constant disgust for her.

A friend of mine that is abroad undertook recently an axam to á
enter on University in Dallas, and was approved.

I felt afraid of losing somebody I love to another person because á
I was an incomprehensive person and lots of time I fight with á
this person.

In certain occasion I have a fight with my boyfriend. During the á
fight I closed the door at his face. He went away but came back á
next day.

Last year, when I took the college entrance examinations I á
failed the FUVEST. It was for me the most frustrating situation á
because I had studied all year long, and only thought about this.

In a certain occasion I saw a dog in the street eating something á
so strange gooey that I wasn't able to eat lunch because I á
remembered the scene all the time.
When I knew about my first job.
When I was just to be divorced.
My mother in law slept in my bed.
A terrible fight that I provoked with my friend.

In the last year of the high school we had a huge fight between á
my group and the graduation commission (two students of my á
classroom) because they accused us unjustly of a gossip about á
them.

When I was 10/11 years old my father travelled very much for his á
work (he passed three months away from home).

I saw a film where snakes were crawling everywhere. I felt them á
crawling over all my body with that ... skins. The noise that á
they did disturbed me very much.
When I got a small present form a person I like very much.

When a friend of mine discussed with me, I felt fear of losing á
her. This occurred because we had a missunderstanding between á
mutual colleagues.

When a boy tried to fool me so he would be OK trying to show me á
that he is a gook boy.
